---
title: Configuring Ops Manager Director for VMware vSphere
---

Refer to the following procedure for help configuring the Ops Manager Director for VMware vSphere product tile.

1. Log in to Pivotal CF Operations Manager.

1. Click the **Ops Manager Director for VMware vSphere** tile.

    <%= image_tag("vsphere-tile.png") %>

1. Select **vCenter credentials**, enter your vCenter IP and credentials, and click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vcenter-credentials.png") %>

    **Note**: This user must have create and delete privileges for VMs and folders.

1. Select **vSphere configuration**, specify the installation resources, and
click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vsphere-configuration.png") %>

1. Select **Network configuration**, enter the vSphere network name, subnet, Pivotal CF IP ranges, DNS, and
Gateway settings, and click **Save**.
The Pivotal CF VMs will use the IP range you specify.
**Excluded IP Ranges** are blacklisted from the installation.

    <%= image_tag("network-configuration.png") %>

1. Select **NTP servers**, enter a comma-delimited list of time server
addresses, and click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("ntp-servers.png") %>

1. Select **Health Monitor**. If you have installed and configured the Ops Metrics product, enter the Metrics IP address.

    <%= image_tag("health-monitor.png") %>

1. Select **System Settings**, check or uncheck **Enable VM resurrector
plugin**, and click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("resurrector.png") %>

1. Select **Post Install Hooks**, accept the default or make necessary changes, and click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("post-install.png") %>

1. Select **Resource Sizes**, accept the defaults or make necessary changes, and
click **Save**.

    <%= image_tag("vsphere-resources.png") %>

1. Click the **Installation Dashboard** link to return to the Installation
Dashboard.

